:QUOTE
A precise prompt is the difference between noise and a vision.

:INFO
Crafting Effective Midjourney Prompts
Midjourney responds to structured prompts that combine subject, environment, lighting, style, and technical parameters. Understanding how each component influences output lets you iterate faster and achieve consistent results.

:COUNTER.half
22 Aspect Ratios
Supported via the --ar parameter
|
:COUNTER.half
0 to 1000
Stylize range controlling artistic interpretation

:PATH
Prompt Structure
Lead with subject, follow with environment and mood, then add style keywords and close with technical parameters.

:PATH
Style Keywords
Reference art movements, photographers, or visual styles. Combine two or three for a hybrid aesthetic rather than one dominant style.

:CHECKLIST
Prompt Engineering Checklist
[ ] Define core subject clearly
[ ] Add lighting descriptor (golden hour, studio, overcast)
[ ] Include medium or style keyword
[ ] Set aspect ratio with --ar
[ ] Adjust stylize value if output is too literal or too abstract
[ ] Use negative prompt with --no for unwanted elements

:NOTE
Save your best-performing prompts in a dedicated file. Over time this becomes a personal prompt library you can remix for new projects without starting from scratch each session.

